{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"name":"","display_name":""},"language_info":{"name":"python"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"nvidiaTeslaT4","dataSources":[{"sourceType":"datasetVersion","sourceId":15685078,"datasetId":10045196,"databundleVersionId":16623279},{"sourceType":"datasetVersion","sourceId":15336285,"datasetId":9809498,"databundleVersionId":16244466}],"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":true}},"nbformat_minor":5,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"id":"beb33531","cell_type":"markdown","source":"# SimCLR — Multi-Anatomy MRI Anomaly Detection\n\nThis notebook trains **three SimCLR models** for artifact detection:\n\n| # | Anatomy | Dataset | Description |\n|---|---------|---------|-------------|\n| 1 | **Knee** | FastMRI (preprocessed) | Single anatomy, single contrast |\n| 2 | **Brain** | IXI (balanced T1 + T2) | Single anatomy, balanced contrast |\n| 3 | **Combined** | Both datasets merged | Multi-anatomy generalist model |\n\n## Architecture (Standard SimCLR — Chen et al., ICML 2020)\n- **ResNet-50** encoder — standard SimCLR backbone (2048-d output)\n- **2-layer projection head** — 2048 → 2048 (BN+ReLU) → 128\n- **NT-Xent loss** — temperature τ = 0.5\n- **Balanced brain sampling** — same deterministic subset as MAE/DINO notebooks\n\n## Consistency with MAE/DINO\n| Setting | SimCLR | MAE | DINO |\n|---------|--------|-----|------|\n| Image size | 192×192 | 192×192 | 192×192 |\n| Effective batch | 256 | 256 | 256 |\n| Epochs | 20 | 20 | 20 |\n| Brain sampling | Balanced (same) | Balanced (same) | Balanced (same) |\n| Evaluation | kNN + collapse check + t-SNE | Same | Same |\n\n## Time Budget (~12h total)\n| Phase | Est. Time |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Knee (20 epochs + analysis) | ~2h |\n| Brain (20 epochs + analysis) | ~2h |\n| Combined (20 epochs + analysis) | ~4h |\n| **Total** | **~8h** |","metadata":{}},{"id":"5dfba9fd","cell_type":"code","source":"import os\nimport math\nimport time\nimport gc\nimport numpy as np\nimport random\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nimport scipy.ndimage\n\nimport torch\nimport torch.nn as nn\nimport torch.nn.functional as F\nfrom torch.utils.data import Dataset, DataLoader\n\nfrom torchvision.models import resnet50\n\nfrom tqdm import tqdm\nfrom sklearn.neighbors import NearestNeighbors\nfrom sklearn.manifold import TSNE\n\n# ── Reproducibility ──\nSEED = 42\nrandom.seed(SEED)\nnp.random.seed(SEED)\ntorch.manual_seed(SEED)\ntorch.cuda.manual_seed_all(SEED)\n\ndevice = \"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\"\nprint(\"Device:\", device)\nif device == \"cuda\":\n    print(torch.cuda.get_device_name(0))\n    print(f\"Memory: {torch.cuda.get_device_properties(0).total_memory / 1e9:.1f} GB\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"32e63932","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Hyperparameters\n\nFollowing the original SimCLR paper (Chen et al., ICML 2020):\n- **ResNet-50** encoder (2048-d) — standard SimCLR backbone\n- **Temperature τ = 0.5** — recommended for effective batch size 256\n- **2-layer projection head** — 2048 → 2048 → 128 (paper standard)\n- **20 epochs** — consistent with MAE and DINO\n- **LR 1e-3** — AdamW with cosine decay\n- **Warmup 2 epochs** — linear warmup","metadata":{}},{"id":"7e452a4c","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Hyperparameters (shared across all 3 models)\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nBATCH_SIZE     = 64\nGRAD_ACCUM     = 4            # effective batch = 64 × 4 = 256\nEPOCHS         = 20           # same as MAE and DINO\nBASE_LR        = 1e-3         # AdamW with cosine decay\nWARMUP_EPOCHS  = 2\nTEMPERATURE    = 0.5          # SimCLR paper standard for batch 256\nWEIGHT_DECAY   = 1e-4\nK_NEIGHBORS    = 5\nNUM_WORKERS    = 4\nIMG_SIZE       = 192\nPROJ_DIM       = 128          # projection output (paper standard)\nPROJ_HIDDEN    = 2048         # projection hidden = encoder output dim\nENCODER_DIM    = 2048         # ResNet-50 output dimension\n\nprint(f\"Effective batch size: {BATCH_SIZE * GRAD_ACCUM}\")\nprint(f\"Real negatives per step: {2 * BATCH_SIZE - 2}\")\nprint(f\"Epochs per model: {EPOCHS}\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"cc13d428","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Data Pipeline\n\n### Balanced Brain Sampling\nSame deterministic `get_balanced_paths()` as MAE and DINO notebooks — identical brain subset.\n\n### SimCLR Augmentation Strategy\nFollowing SimCLR paper + MRI-specific transforms:\n- Random crop, horizontal/vertical flip\n- Rotation ±15°, intensity jitter\n- Gaussian blur, Gaussian noise\n- Bias field simulation (MRI-specific)\n- Random cutout (forces global context)","metadata":{}},{"id":"268a9636","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Balanced Sampling + Augmentations\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n\ndef get_balanced_paths(root_dir, target_total=None):\n    \"\"\"Deterministic balanced subsampling — IDENTICAL to MAE/DINO notebooks.\"\"\"\n    groups = {}\n    for dirpath, _, filenames in os.walk(root_dir):\n        npy_files = sorted(f for f in filenames if f.endswith('.npy'))\n        if npy_files:\n            folder = os.path.basename(dirpath)\n            groups[folder] = [os.path.join(dirpath, f) for f in npy_files]\n\n    if not groups:\n        return [], []\n\n    if target_total is None:\n        paths, labels = [], []\n        for folder in sorted(groups):\n            paths.extend(groups[folder])\n            labels.extend([folder] * len(groups[folder]))\n        return paths, labels\n\n    n_groups = len(groups)\n    target_per_group = target_total // n_groups\n\n    paths, labels = [], []\n    for folder in sorted(groups):\n        group_paths = groups[folder]\n        if len(group_paths) <= target_per_group:\n            selected = group_paths\n        else:\n            idx = np.round(np.linspace(0, len(group_paths) - 1, target_per_group)).astype(int)\n            selected = [group_paths[i] for i in idx]\n        paths.extend(selected)\n        labels.extend([folder] * len(selected))\n        print(f\"    {folder}: {len(selected)}/{len(group_paths)} selected\")\n\n    return paths, labels\n\n\nclass SimCLRAugmentMRI:\n    \"\"\"SimCLR augmentations for grayscale MRI.\n    Simulates normal scanner/anatomy variation only — no artifact simulation.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, img_size=192):\n        self.img_size = img_size\n\n    def _apply_once(self, img_np):\n        img = img_np.copy()\n        h, w = img.shape\n\n        # 1. Elastic deformation (p=0.3)\n        if random.random() < 0.3:\n            img = self._elastic_deform(img, alpha=15.0, sigma=4.0)\n\n        # 2. Random affine: rotation ±20° + scale 0.7–1.0 + translation ±5%\n        angle = random.uniform(-20, 20)\n        scale = random.uniform(0.7, 1.0)\n        tx = random.uniform(-0.05, 0.05) * w\n        ty = random.uniform(-0.05, 0.05) * h\n        img = self._affine_transform(img, angle, scale, tx, ty)\n\n        # 3. Random crop to target size\n        img = self._random_crop(img, self.img_size)\n\n        # 4. Horizontal flip (p=0.5)\n        if random.random() < 0.5:\n            img = np.flip(img, axis=1).copy()\n\n        # 5. Bias field simulation (p=0.3)\n        if random.random() < 0.3:\n            img = self._simulate_bias_field(img)\n\n        # 6. Gamma correction (p=0.4)\n        if random.random() < 0.4:\n            gamma = random.uniform(0.7, 1.5)\n            img = np.clip(img, 0, 1)\n            img = np.power(img, gamma)\n\n        # 7. Intensity scaling + shift (p=0.6)\n        if random.random() < 0.6:\n            gain = random.uniform(0.75, 1.25)\n            bias = random.uniform(-0.1, 0.1)\n            img = img * gain + bias\n\n        # 8. Gaussian blur (p=0.5) — SimCLR paper uses 50% probability\n        if random.random() < 0.5:\n            sigma = random.uniform(0.1, 2.0)\n            img = scipy.ndimage.gaussian_filter(img, sigma=sigma)\n\n        # 9. Gaussian noise (p=0.3)\n        if random.random() < 0.3:\n            noise_std = random.uniform(0.01, 0.04)\n            img = img + noise_std * np.random.randn(*img.shape).astype(np.float32)\n\n        # 10. Random cutout (p=0.3)\n        if random.random() < 0.3:\n            img = self._random_cutout(img, max_ratio=0.2)\n\n        img = np.clip(img, 0.0, 1.0).astype(np.float32)\n        return torch.from_numpy(img).unsqueeze(0)  # (1, H, W)\n\n    def __call__(self, x):\n        return self._apply_once(x), self._apply_once(x)\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def _elastic_deform(img, alpha=15.0, sigma=4.0):\n        shape = img.shape\n        dx = scipy.ndimage.gaussian_filter(np.random.randn(*shape), sigma) * alpha\n        dy = scipy.ndimage.gaussian_filter(np.random.randn(*shape), sigma) * alpha\n        y, x = np.meshgrid(np.arange(shape[0]), np.arange(shape[1]), indexing='ij')\n        coords = [np.clip(y + dy, 0, shape[0] - 1), np.clip(x + dx, 0, shape[1] - 1)]\n        return scipy.ndimage.map_coordinates(img, coords, order=1, mode='reflect').astype(np.float32)\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def _affine_transform(img, angle, scale, tx, ty):\n        h, w = img.shape\n        cos_a = math.cos(math.radians(angle)) * scale\n        sin_a = math.sin(math.radians(angle)) * scale\n        cx, cy = w / 2, h / 2\n        matrix = np.array([[cos_a, sin_a], [-sin_a, cos_a]]) / (scale * scale)\n        offset = np.array([cy - cos_a * cy - sin_a * cx + ty,\n                           cx + sin_a * cy - cos_a * cx + tx])\n        return scipy.ndimage.affine_transform(img, matrix, offset=offset,\n                                               order=1, mode='reflect').astype(np.float32)\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def _random_crop(img, target_size):\n        h, w = img.shape\n        if h < target_size or w < target_size:\n            pad_h = max(0, target_size - h)\n            pad_w = max(0, target_size - w)\n            img = np.pad(img, ((0, pad_h), (0, pad_w)), mode='reflect')\n            h, w = img.shape\n        y = random.randint(0, h - target_size)\n        x = random.randint(0, w - target_size)\n        return img[y:y + target_size, x:x + target_size]\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def _simulate_bias_field(img):\n        h, w = img.shape\n        x = np.linspace(-1, 1, w)\n        y = np.linspace(-1, 1, h)\n        xv, yv = np.meshgrid(x, y)\n        a = random.uniform(-0.3, 0.3)\n        b = random.uniform(-0.3, 0.3)\n        c = random.uniform(-0.1, 0.1)\n        bias = 1.0 + a * xv + b * yv + c * (xv**2 + yv**2)\n        return (img * bias).astype(np.float32)\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def _random_cutout(img, max_ratio=0.2):\n        h, w = img.shape\n        ch = int(h * random.uniform(0.05, max_ratio))\n        cw = int(w * random.uniform(0.05, max_ratio))\n        y = random.randint(0, h - ch)\n        x = random.randint(0, w - cw)\n        img = img.copy()\n        img[y:y + ch, x:x + cw] = 0.0\n        return img\n\n\nclass CleanTransform:\n    def __call__(self, x):\n        return torch.from_numpy(x).unsqueeze(0).float()\n\n\nclass MRISimCLRDataset(Dataset):\n    \"\"\"Returns two augmented views + label for contrastive training.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, paths, labels, label_map, transform=None, name=\"\"):\n        self.paths = paths\n        self.label_map = label_map\n        self.labels = [label_map[l] for l in labels]\n        self.transform = transform\n        print(f\"  [{name}] {len(paths)} slices | Labels: {label_map}\")\n\n    def __len__(self):\n        return len(self.paths)\n\n    def __getitem__(self, idx):\n        img = np.load(self.paths[idx]).astype(np.float32)\n        x1, x2 = self.transform(img)\n        return x1, x2, self.labels[idx]\n\n\nclass MRICleanDataset(Dataset):\n    \"\"\"Returns clean unaugmented images + labels for feature extraction.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, paths, labels, label_map, transform=None, name=\"\"):\n        self.paths = paths\n        self.label_map = label_map\n        self.labels = [label_map[l] for l in labels]\n        self.transform = transform or CleanTransform()\n        print(f\"  [{name}] {len(paths)} slices | Labels: {label_map}\")\n\n    def __len__(self):\n        return len(self.paths)\n\n    def __getitem__(self, idx):\n        img = np.load(self.paths[idx]).astype(np.float32)\n        return self.transform(img), self.labels[idx]","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"eb5700e2","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Model Architecture\n\n### Encoder: ResNet-50 (SimCLR paper standard)\n- 1-channel input (conv1 adapted for grayscale)\n- Standard ResNet-50 layers 1–4 + global average pooling\n- Output: **2048-d** vector\n\n### Projection Head (SimCLR paper: 2-layer MLP)\n- Linear 2048 → 2048 (BN + ReLU) → 128\n- Discarded after training — only encoder features used for evaluation\n\n### NT-Xent Loss\n- Temperature τ = 0.5\n- L2-normalized embeddings\n- Forced fp32 computation","metadata":{}},{"id":"18b68f41","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Model Definition — Standard SimCLR (Chen et al., ICML 2020)\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nclass Encoder(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"ResNet-50 encoder adapted for 1-channel grayscale MRI.\n    Standard SimCLR backbone — output 2048-d.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self):\n        super().__init__()\n        backbone = resnet50(weights=None)\n        # Adapt conv1 for 1-channel grayscale input\n        backbone.conv1 = nn.Conv2d(1, 64, kernel_size=7, stride=2, padding=3, bias=False)\n        self.features = nn.Sequential(\n            backbone.conv1, backbone.bn1, backbone.relu, backbone.maxpool,\n            backbone.layer1, backbone.layer2, backbone.layer3, backbone.layer4,\n            backbone.avgpool,\n        )\n\n    def forward(self, x):\n        return self.features(x).flatten(1)  # (B, 2048)\n\n\nclass ProjectionHead(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"2-layer projection head (SimCLR paper standard).\n    2048 → 2048 (BN+ReLU) → 128\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, in_dim=2048, hidden_dim=2048, out_dim=128):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.net = nn.Sequential(\n            nn.Linear(in_dim, hidden_dim),\n            nn.BatchNorm1d(hidden_dim),\n            nn.ReLU(inplace=True),\n            nn.Linear(hidden_dim, out_dim),\n        )\n\n    def forward(self, x):\n        return self.net(x)\n\n\nclass NTXentLoss(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"Normalized Temperature-scaled Cross-Entropy Loss (SimCLR).\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, temperature=0.5):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.temperature = temperature\n\n    @torch.amp.autocast(\"cuda\", enabled=False)\n    def forward(self, z1, z2):\n        z1 = F.normalize(z1.float(), dim=1)\n        z2 = F.normalize(z2.float(), dim=1)\n\n        N = z1.size(0)\n        z = torch.cat([z1, z2], dim=0)\n        sim = torch.mm(z, z.T) / self.temperature\n\n        mask = torch.eye(2 * N, dtype=torch.bool, device=z.device)\n        sim.masked_fill_(mask, float(\"-inf\"))\n\n        positives = torch.cat([torch.diag(sim, N), torch.diag(sim, -N)])\n        loss = -positives + torch.logsumexp(sim, dim=1)\n        return loss.mean()\n\n\ndef count_params(model):\n    return sum(p.numel() for p in model.parameters())\n\n\n# Architecture check\n_enc = Encoder()\n_proj = ProjectionHead(ENCODER_DIM, PROJ_HIDDEN, PROJ_DIM)\nprint(f\"Encoder params: {count_params(_enc):,} ({count_params(_enc)/1e6:.1f}M)\")\nprint(f\"Projection params: {count_params(_proj):,} ({count_params(_proj)/1e6:.1f}M)\")\nprint(f\"Total: {(count_params(_enc)+count_params(_proj)):,} ({(count_params(_enc)+count_params(_proj))/1e6:.1f}M)\")\n\nwith torch.no_grad():\n    _out = _enc(torch.randn(2, 1, 192, 192))\n    print(f\"Encoder output: {_out.shape}\")\n    _z = _proj(_out)\n    print(f\"Projection output: {_z.shape}\")\ndel _enc, _proj, _out, _z","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"04423a61","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Training Infrastructure\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nMAX_GRAD_NORM = 1.0\nTOTAL_TIME_BUDGET = 12 * 3600\nSESSION_START = time.time()\n\n\ndef log_time_budget(phase=\"\"):\n    elapsed = time.time() - SESSION_START\n    remaining = TOTAL_TIME_BUDGET - elapsed\n    print(f\"⏱ [{phase}] Elapsed: {elapsed/3600:.2f}h | Remaining: {remaining/3600:.2f}h \"\n          f\"| Budget used: {100*elapsed/TOTAL_TIME_BUDGET:.1f}%\")\n    if remaining < 1800:\n        print(\"  ⚠️ WARNING: Less than 30 min remaining!\")\n    return remaining\n\n\ndef log_gpu_memory(prefix=\"\"):\n    if device == \"cuda\":\n        alloc = torch.cuda.memory_allocated() / 1e9\n        peak = torch.cuda.max_memory_allocated() / 1e9\n        total = torch.cuda.get_device_properties(0).total_memory / 1e9\n        print(f\"  🖥 GPU [{prefix}]: {alloc:.2f}/{total:.1f} GB (peak: {peak:.2f} GB)\")\n\n\ndef clear_gpu():\n    gc.collect()\n    if torch.cuda.is_available():\n        torch.cuda.empty_cache()\n        torch.cuda.reset_peak_memory_stats()\n    log_gpu_memory(\"after clear\")\n    log_time_budget(\"GPU cleared\")\n\n\ndef train_epoch(encoder, projector, loader, criterion, optimizer, scaler):\n    encoder.train()\n    projector.train()\n    total_loss = 0.0\n    num_batches = len(loader)\n    log_interval = max(1, num_batches // 5)\n    optimizer.zero_grad()\n    epoch_start = time.time()\n\n    for step, (x1, x2, _) in enumerate(loader):\n        x1, x2 = x1.to(device), x2.to(device)\n\n        with torch.amp.autocast(\"cuda\", enabled=(device == \"cuda\")):\n            z1 = projector(encoder(x1))\n            z2 = projector(encoder(x2))\n            loss = criterion(z1, z2) / GRAD_ACCUM\n\n        scaler.scale(loss).backward()\n\n        if (step + 1) % GRAD_ACCUM == 0 or (step + 1) == num_batches:\n            scaler.unscale_(optimizer)\n            torch.nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(\n                list(encoder.parameters()) + list(projector.parameters()),\n                MAX_GRAD_NORM,\n            )\n            scaler.step(optimizer)\n            scaler.update()\n            optimizer.zero_grad()\n\n        total_loss += loss.item() * GRAD_ACCUM\n\n        if (step + 1) % log_interval == 0:\n            avg_loss = total_loss / (step + 1)\n            elapsed = time.time() - epoch_start\n            batch_rate = (step + 1) / elapsed\n            eta_epoch = (num_batches - step - 1) / batch_rate\n            print(f\"    batch {step+1}/{num_batches} | loss={avg_loss:.4f} | \"\n                  f\"{batch_rate:.1f} batch/s | ETA: {eta_epoch:.0f}s\", end=\"\\r\")\n\n    print(\" \" * 80, end=\"\\r\")\n    return total_loss / num_batches\n\n\n@torch.no_grad()\ndef eval_epoch(encoder, projector, loader, criterion):\n    encoder.eval()\n    projector.eval()\n    total_loss = 0.0\n    for x1, x2, _ in loader:\n        x1, x2 = x1.to(device), x2.to(device)\n        with torch.amp.autocast(\"cuda\", enabled=(device == \"cuda\")):\n            z1 = projector(encoder(x1))\n            z2 = projector(encoder(x2))\n            loss = criterion(z1, z2)\n        total_loss += loss.item()\n    return total_loss / len(loader)\n\n\n@torch.no_grad()\ndef extract_features(encoder, loader):\n    \"\"\"Extract L2-normalized encoder features.\"\"\"\n    encoder.eval()\n    feats, labels = [], []\n    for x, y in tqdm(loader, desc=\"Extracting features\"):\n        x = x.to(device)\n        with torch.amp.autocast(\"cuda\", enabled=(device == \"cuda\")):\n            f = encoder(x).float()\n        f = F.normalize(f, dim=1)\n        feats.append(f.cpu().numpy())\n        labels.append(y.numpy())\n    return np.concatenate(feats), np.concatenate(labels)","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"a194f58d","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Full Training Loop\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\ndef train_simclr(train_loader, val_loader, save_dir, model_name=\"SimCLR\"):\n    os.makedirs(save_dir, exist_ok=True)\n\n    remaining = log_time_budget(f\"START {model_name}\")\n    if remaining < 3600:\n        print(\"  ⚠️ CRITICAL: Less than 1h remaining!\")\n\n    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n    print(f\"  🚀 Training: {model_name}\")\n    print(f\"  📁 Save dir: {save_dir}\")\n    print(f\"  📊 Train batches: {len(train_loader)}\")\n    print(f\"  ⚙️  Config: {EPOCHS}ep, BS={BATCH_SIZE}, accum={GRAD_ACCUM}, τ={TEMPERATURE}\")\n    print(f\"{'='*60}\\n\")\n\n    encoder = Encoder().to(device)\n    projector = ProjectionHead(ENCODER_DIM, PROJ_HIDDEN, PROJ_DIM).to(device)\n\n    total_params = count_params(encoder) + count_params(projector)\n    print(f\"  Parameters: {total_params:,} ({total_params/1e6:.1f}M)\")\n    log_gpu_memory(\"model loaded\")\n\n    optimizer = torch.optim.AdamW(\n        list(encoder.parameters()) + list(projector.parameters()),\n        lr=BASE_LR, weight_decay=WEIGHT_DECAY,\n    )\n\n    def lr_lambda(epoch):\n        if epoch < WARMUP_EPOCHS:\n            return (epoch + 1) / WARMUP_EPOCHS\n        progress = (epoch - WARMUP_EPOCHS) / max(EPOCHS - WARMUP_EPOCHS, 1)\n        return 0.5 * (1.0 + math.cos(math.pi * progress))\n\n    scheduler = torch.optim.lr_scheduler.LambdaLR(optimizer, lr_lambda)\n    criterion = NTXentLoss(temperature=TEMPERATURE)\n    scaler = torch.amp.GradScaler(\"cuda\", enabled=(device == \"cuda\"))\n\n    history = {\"train_loss\": [], \"val_loss\": [], \"lr\": [], \"epoch_time\": []}\n    best_val_loss = float(\"inf\")\n    total_start = time.time()\n\n    for epoch in range(EPOCHS):\n        epoch_start = time.time()\n\n        t_loss = train_epoch(encoder, projector, train_loader, criterion, optimizer, scaler)\n        v_loss = eval_epoch(encoder, projector, val_loader, criterion)\n        scheduler.step()\n\n        epoch_time = time.time() - epoch_start\n        lr_now = scheduler.get_last_lr()[0]\n        history[\"train_loss\"].append(t_loss)\n        history[\"val_loss\"].append(v_loss)\n        history[\"lr\"].append(lr_now)\n        history[\"epoch_time\"].append(epoch_time)\n\n        elapsed_session = time.time() - SESSION_START\n        remaining_session = TOTAL_TIME_BUDGET - elapsed_session\n\n        print(f\"  [{model_name}] Epoch {epoch+1:2d}/{EPOCHS} │ \"\n              f\"train={t_loss:.4f} val={v_loss:.4f} │ lr={lr_now:.6f} │ \"\n              f\"{epoch_time:.0f}s/ep │ budget left: {remaining_session/3600:.2f}h\")\n\n        if v_loss < best_val_loss:\n            best_val_loss = v_loss\n            torch.save({\n                \"epoch\": epoch + 1,\n                \"encoder\": encoder.state_dict(),\n                \"projector\": projector.state_dict(),\n                \"val_loss\": v_loss,\n            }, os.path.join(save_dir, \"best.pt\"))\n            print(f\"       ↑ New best! (val_loss={v_loss:.4f})\")\n\n        if (epoch + 1) % 5 == 0:\n            torch.save({\n                \"epoch\": epoch + 1,\n                \"encoder\": encoder.state_dict(),\n                \"projector\": projector.state_dict(),\n            }, os.path.join(save_dir, f\"epoch_{epoch+1}.pt\"))\n            print(f\"       💾 Checkpoint: epoch_{epoch+1}.pt\")\n            log_gpu_memory(f\"epoch {epoch+1}\")\n\n        if remaining_session < 1800 and epoch < EPOCHS - 1:\n            print(f\"  ⚠️ TIME: {remaining_session/60:.0f} min left! Stopping at epoch {epoch+1}.\")\n            break\n\n    total_time = time.time() - total_start\n    torch.save({\n        \"epoch\": epoch + 1,\n        \"encoder\": encoder.state_dict(),\n        \"projector\": projector.state_dict(),\n        \"history\": history,\n    }, os.path.join(save_dir, \"final.pt\"))\n\n    print(f\"\\n  ✅ {model_name} complete in {total_time/60:.1f} min ({total_time/3600:.2f}h)\")\n    print(f\"     Best val loss: {best_val_loss:.4f}\")\n    print(f\"     Avg epoch time: {np.mean(history['epoch_time']):.1f}s\")\n    log_time_budget(f\"END {model_name}\")\n\n    best_ckpt = torch.load(os.path.join(save_dir, \"best.pt\"), map_location=device, weights_only=False)\n    encoder.load_state_dict(best_ckpt[\"encoder\"])\n\n    return encoder, projector, history","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"a3743214","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Full Analysis Pipeline\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\ndef run_full_analysis(encoder, train_clean_loader, val_clean_loader,\n                      val_clean_dataset, history, save_dir, model_name):\n    analysis_start = time.time()\n    log_time_budget(f\"ANALYSIS START {model_name}\")\n\n    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n    print(f\"  📈 Analysis: {model_name}\")\n    print(f\"{'='*60}\")\n\n    # ── 1. Training Curves ──\n    print(\"\\n[1/10] Training curves...\")\n    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 4, figsize=(22, 5))\n    fig.suptitle(f\"{model_name} — Training Curves\", fontsize=14, y=1.02)\n\n    axes[0].plot(history[\"train_loss\"], label=\"Train\", linewidth=2)\n    axes[0].plot(history[\"val_loss\"], label=\"Val\", linewidth=2)\n    axes[0].set_xlabel(\"Epoch\"); axes[0].set_ylabel(\"NT-Xent Loss\")\n    axes[0].set_title(\"Loss\"); axes[0].legend(); axes[0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n\n    axes[1].plot(history[\"lr\"], linewidth=2, color=\"green\")\n    axes[1].set_xlabel(\"Epoch\"); axes[1].set_ylabel(\"LR\")\n    axes[1].set_title(\"Learning Rate\"); axes[1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n\n    gap = [v - t for t, v in zip(history[\"train_loss\"], history[\"val_loss\"])]\n    axes[2].plot(gap, linewidth=2, color=\"red\")\n    axes[2].axhline(0, color=\"gray\", ls=\"--\", alpha=0.5)\n    axes[2].set_xlabel(\"Epoch\"); axes[2].set_ylabel(\"Val - Train\")\n    axes[2].set_title(\"Generalization Gap\"); axes[2].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n\n    axes[3].plot(history[\"epoch_time\"], linewidth=2, color=\"brown\")\n    axes[3].set_xlabel(\"Epoch\"); axes[3].set_ylabel(\"Seconds\")\n    axes[3].set_title(\"Epoch Time\"); axes[3].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n\n    fig.tight_layout()\n    fig.savefig(os.path.join(save_dir, \"training_curves.png\"), dpi=150, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n    plt.show()\n\n    # ── 2. Feature Extraction ──\n    print(\"[2/10] Extracting features...\")\n    feat_start = time.time()\n    train_feats, train_labels = extract_features(encoder, train_clean_loader)\n    val_feats, val_labels = extract_features(encoder, val_clean_loader)\n    print(f\"  Train: {train_feats.shape}, Val: {val_feats.shape} ({time.time()-feat_start:.1f}s)\")\n\n    # ── 3. Collapse Check ──\n    print(\"[3/10] Collapse check...\")\n    n_check = min(2000, len(train_feats))\n    for name, feats in [(\"Train\", train_feats[:n_check]), (\"Val\", val_feats[:n_check])]:\n        std = np.std(feats, axis=0).mean()\n        sim_mat = np.dot(feats, feats.T)\n        off_diag = sim_mat[np.triu_indices_from(sim_mat, k=1)]\n        mean_sim = off_diag.mean()\n        s_std = \"✅\" if std > 0.01 else \"⚠️ COLLAPSE\"\n        s_sim = \"✅\" if mean_sim < 0.9 else \"⚠️ HIGH\"\n        print(f\"  {name}: STD={std:.4f} {s_std} | Mean cos sim={mean_sim:.4f} {s_sim}\")\n\n    # ── 4. kNN Anomaly Scores ──\n    print(\"[4/10] kNN anomaly scores...\")\n    nn_model = NearestNeighbors(n_neighbors=K_NEIGHBORS, metric=\"cosine\")\n    nn_model.fit(train_feats)\n    train_knn = nn_model.kneighbors(train_feats)[0].mean(axis=1)\n    val_knn = nn_model.kneighbors(val_feats)[0].mean(axis=1)\n    print(f\"  Train kNN — mean: {train_knn.mean():.4f}, std: {train_knn.std():.4f}\")\n    print(f\"  Val kNN   — mean: {val_knn.mean():.4f}, std: {val_knn.std():.4f}\")\n\n    # ── 5. Score Distributions ──\n    print(\"[5/10] Score distributions...\")\n    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\n    fig.suptitle(f\"{model_name} — kNN Anomaly Score Distributions\", fontsize=14, y=1.02)\n    axes[0].hist(train_knn, bins=60, alpha=0.7, color=\"steelblue\", edgecolor=\"white\")\n    axes[0].set_title(\"Train — kNN Distance\"); axes[0].set_xlabel(\"Cosine Dist\")\n    axes[1].hist(val_knn, bins=60, alpha=0.7, color=\"coral\", edgecolor=\"white\")\n    axes[1].set_title(\"Val — kNN Distance\"); axes[1].set_xlabel(\"Cosine Dist\")\n    fig.tight_layout()\n    fig.savefig(os.path.join(save_dir, \"anomaly_scores.png\"), dpi=150, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n    plt.show()\n\n    # ── 6. Threshold Analysis ──\n    print(\"[6/10] Threshold analysis...\")\n    print(\"  kNN-based:\")\n    for pct in [90, 95, 97.5, 99]:\n        thresh = np.percentile(train_knn, pct)\n        flagged = (val_knn > thresh).sum()\n        print(f\"    p{pct}: thresh={thresh:.4f} → {flagged}/{len(val_knn)} val flagged \"\n              f\"({100*flagged/len(val_knn):.1f}%)\")\n\n    # ── 7. t-SNE ──\n    print(\"[7/10] t-SNE...\")\n    tsne_start = time.time()\n    N_TSNE = min(3000, len(val_feats))\n    tsne = TSNE(n_components=2, perplexity=30, random_state=SEED, max_iter=1000)\n    emb = tsne.fit_transform(val_feats[:N_TSNE])\n    labels_sub = val_labels[:N_TSNE]\n    knn_sub = val_knn[:N_TSNE]\n    print(f\"  t-SNE done ({time.time()-tsne_start:.1f}s)\")\n\n    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(18, 6))\n    fig.suptitle(f\"{model_name} — t-SNE Embeddings\", fontsize=14, y=1.02)\n    axes[0].scatter(emb[:, 0], emb[:, 1], s=3, alpha=0.5, c=\"steelblue\")\n    axes[0].set_title(\"Unsupervised\"); axes[0].set_xticks([]); axes[0].set_yticks([])\n    sc1 = axes[1].scatter(emb[:, 0], emb[:, 1], s=3, alpha=0.5, c=labels_sub, cmap=\"coolwarm\")\n    axes[1].set_title(\"By Label\"); axes[1].set_xticks([]); axes[1].set_yticks([])\n    plt.colorbar(sc1, ax=axes[1], shrink=0.8)\n    sc2 = axes[2].scatter(emb[:, 0], emb[:, 1], s=3, alpha=0.5, c=knn_sub, cmap=\"YlOrRd\")\n    axes[2].set_title(\"kNN Score\"); axes[2].set_xticks([]); axes[2].set_yticks([])\n    plt.colorbar(sc2, ax=axes[2], shrink=0.8)\n    fig.tight_layout()\n    fig.savefig(os.path.join(save_dir, \"tsne.png\"), dpi=150, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n    plt.show()\n\n    # ── 8. Cosine Similarity Distribution ──\n    print(\"[8/10] Cosine similarity distribution...\")\n    subset = torch.tensor(val_feats[:2000])\n    sim_matrix = torch.mm(subset, subset.T).numpy()\n    upper_tri = sim_matrix[np.triu_indices_from(sim_matrix, k=1)]\n    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))\n    ax.hist(upper_tri, bins=100, color=\"mediumpurple\", edgecolor=\"white\", alpha=0.8)\n    ax.axvline(upper_tri.mean(), color=\"red\", ls=\"--\", label=f\"Mean: {upper_tri.mean():.3f}\")\n    ax.set_title(f\"{model_name} — Pairwise Cosine Similarity\")\n    ax.set_xlabel(\"Cosine Similarity\"); ax.legend()\n    fig.tight_layout()\n    fig.savefig(os.path.join(save_dir, \"similarity_dist.png\"), dpi=150, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n    plt.show()\n\n    # ── 9. NN Retrieval ──\n    print(\"[9/10] Nearest neighbor retrieval...\")\n    nn_vis = NearestNeighbors(n_neighbors=6, metric=\"cosine\").fit(val_feats)\n    indices = random.sample(range(len(val_feats)), 3)\n    fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 6, figsize=(15, 7.5))\n    fig.suptitle(f\"{model_name} — NN Retrieval\", fontsize=14, y=1.02)\n    for row, q_idx in enumerate(indices):\n        _, nn_idxs = nn_vis.kneighbors([val_feats[q_idx]])\n        for col, idx in enumerate(nn_idxs[0]):\n            img = np.load(val_clean_dataset.paths[idx])\n            axes[row][col].imshow(img, cmap=\"gray\", vmin=0, vmax=1)\n            axes[row][col].axis(\"off\")\n            axes[row][col].set_title(\"Query\" if col == 0 else f\"NN-{col}\", fontsize=9)\n    fig.tight_layout()\n    fig.savefig(os.path.join(save_dir, \"nn_retrieval.png\"), dpi=150, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n    plt.show()\n\n    # ── 10. Top Anomalies ──\n    print(\"[10/10] Top anomalies...\")\n    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 5, figsize=(15, 6))\n    fig.suptitle(f\"{model_name} — Top-10 Anomalies (by kNN distance)\", fontsize=14)\n    top_idx = np.argsort(val_knn)[-10:][::-1]\n    for i, idx in enumerate(top_idx):\n        ax = axes[i // 5][i % 5]\n        img = np.load(val_clean_dataset.paths[idx])\n        ax.imshow(img, cmap=\"gray\", vmin=0, vmax=1)\n        ax.set_title(f\"kNN={val_knn[idx]:.4f}\", fontsize=8)\n        ax.axis(\"off\")\n    fig.tight_layout()\n    fig.savefig(os.path.join(save_dir, \"top_anomalies.png\"), dpi=150, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n    plt.show()\n\n    # ── Save ──\n    np.savez(\n        os.path.join(save_dir, \"scoring.npz\"),\n        train_knn=train_knn, val_knn=val_knn,\n        train_feats=train_feats, val_feats=val_feats,\n        train_labels=train_labels, val_labels=val_labels,\n        threshold_knn_p95=np.percentile(train_knn, 95),\n    )\n\n    print(f\"\\n  ✅ Analysis complete in {(time.time()-analysis_start)/60:.1f} min\")\n    print(f\"  📁 Files: {os.listdir(save_dir)}\")\n    log_time_budget(f\"ANALYSIS END {model_name}\")\n\n    return train_feats, val_feats, train_knn, val_knn","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"59603c30","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Discover dataset paths\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nKNEE_ROOT = \"/kaggle/input/preprocessed-fastmri-knee\"\nBRAIN_ROOT = \"/kaggle/input/preprocessed-ixi-brain\"\n\ndef show_tree(path, prefix=\"\", max_depth=3, depth=0):\n    if depth >= max_depth:\n        return\n    try:\n        entries = sorted(os.listdir(path))\n    except (PermissionError, FileNotFoundError) as e:\n        print(f\"{prefix}⚠️ {e}\")\n        return\n    dirs = [e for e in entries if os.path.isdir(os.path.join(path, e))]\n    files = [e for e in entries if os.path.isfile(os.path.join(path, e))]\n    if files:\n        npy = [f for f in files if f.endswith('.npy')]\n        if npy:\n            print(f\"{prefix}📄 {len(npy)} .npy files (e.g., {npy[0]})\")\n        for f in [x for x in files if not x.endswith('.npy')][:3]:\n            print(f\"{prefix}📄 {f}\")\n    for d in dirs:\n        print(f\"{prefix}📁 {d}/\")\n        show_tree(os.path.join(path, d), prefix + \"    \", max_depth, depth + 1)\n\nprint(\"=\" * 50)\nprint(\"KNEE Dataset:\")\nprint(\"=\" * 50)\nshow_tree(KNEE_ROOT)\n\nprint(f\"\\n{'='*50}\")\nprint(\"BRAIN Dataset:\")\nprint(\"=\" * 50)\nshow_tree(BRAIN_ROOT)","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"122ec49c","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Configure Paths + Balanced Brain Sampling\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nKNEE_TRAIN = os.path.join(KNEE_ROOT, \"train\")\nKNEE_VAL   = os.path.join(KNEE_ROOT, \"val\")\nBRAIN_TRAIN = os.path.join(BRAIN_ROOT, \"train\")\nBRAIN_VAL   = os.path.join(BRAIN_ROOT, \"val\")\n\nprint(\"Knee (all):\")\nknee_train_paths, knee_train_labels = get_balanced_paths(KNEE_TRAIN)\nknee_val_paths, knee_val_labels = get_balanced_paths(KNEE_VAL)\nprint(f\"  Train: {len(knee_train_paths)} | Val: {len(knee_val_paths)}\")\n\nprint(f\"\\nBrain (balanced to match knee = {len(knee_train_paths)}):\")\nprint(\"  Train:\")\nbrain_train_paths, brain_train_labels = get_balanced_paths(\n    BRAIN_TRAIN, target_total=len(knee_train_paths))\nprint(\"  Val:\")\nbrain_val_paths, brain_val_labels = get_balanced_paths(\n    BRAIN_VAL, target_total=len(knee_val_paths))\nprint(f\"  Train: {len(brain_train_paths)} | Val: {len(brain_val_paths)}\")\n\nknee_label_map = {l: i for i, l in enumerate(sorted(set(knee_train_labels)))}\nbrain_label_map = {l: i for i, l in enumerate(sorted(set(brain_train_labels)))}\nall_labels = sorted(set(knee_train_labels + brain_train_labels))\ncombined_label_map = {l: i for i, l in enumerate(all_labels)}\n\nprint(f\"\\nLabel maps:\")\nprint(f\"  Knee: {knee_label_map}\")\nprint(f\"  Brain: {brain_label_map}\")\nprint(f\"  Combined: {combined_label_map}\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"2cfe9622","cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n# Part 1: Knee Only (FastMRI)","metadata":{}},{"id":"7df2e71d","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PART 1: KNEE — Data Loaders\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nprint(\"Loading Knee datasets...\")\naug = SimCLRAugmentMRI(IMG_SIZE)\n\nknee_train_ds = MRISimCLRDataset(knee_train_paths, knee_train_labels, knee_label_map,\n                                  transform=aug, name=\"Knee-Train\")\nknee_val_ds = MRISimCLRDataset(knee_val_paths, knee_val_labels, knee_label_map,\n                                transform=aug, name=\"Knee-Val\")\n\nknee_train_loader = DataLoader(knee_train_ds, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True,\n                               num_workers=NUM_WORKERS, pin_memory=True, drop_last=True)\nknee_val_loader = DataLoader(knee_val_ds, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=False,\n                             num_workers=NUM_WORKERS, pin_memory=True)\n\n# Clean loaders for feature extraction\nknee_train_clean = MRICleanDataset(knee_train_paths, knee_train_labels, knee_label_map,\n                                    name=\"Knee-Train-Clean\")\nknee_val_clean = MRICleanDataset(knee_val_paths, knee_val_labels, knee_label_map,\n                                  name=\"Knee-Val-Clean\")\n\nknee_train_clean_loader = DataLoader(knee_train_clean, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE * 2, shuffle=False,\n                                     num_workers=NUM_WORKERS, pin_memory=True)\nknee_val_clean_loader = DataLoader(knee_val_clean, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE * 2, shuffle=False,\n                                   num_workers=NUM_WORKERS, pin_memory=True)\n\nprint(f\"\\nTrain batches: {len(knee_train_loader)}\")\nprint(f\"Knee train: {len(knee_train_ds)} | Val: {len(knee_val_ds)}\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"53b4e505","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PART 1: KNEE — Augmentation Preview\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 5, figsize=(12.5, 5))\nfig.suptitle(\"Knee — SimCLR Augmentation Preview\", fontsize=14, y=1.02)\n\nfor row in range(2):\n    idx = random.randint(0, len(knee_train_clean) - 1)\n    raw = np.load(knee_train_clean.paths[idx]).astype(np.float32)\n    axes[row][0].imshow(raw, cmap=\"gray\", vmin=0, vmax=1)\n    axes[row][0].set_title(\"Original\", fontweight=\"bold\", fontsize=9)\n    axes[row][0].axis(\"off\")\n    for col in range(1, 5):\n        v, _ = aug(raw)\n        axes[row][col].imshow(v[0], cmap=\"gray\", vmin=0, vmax=1)\n        axes[row][col].set_title(f\"View {col}\", fontsize=9)\n        axes[row][col].axis(\"off\")\n\nfig.tight_layout()\nplt.show()","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"9d7903df","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PART 1: KNEE — Train SimCLR\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nKNEE_SAVE = \"/kaggle/working/checkpoints/simclr_knee\"\nknee_encoder, knee_projector, knee_history = train_simclr(\n    knee_train_loader, knee_val_loader, KNEE_SAVE, model_name=\"SimCLR-Knee\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"070e24a3","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PART 1: KNEE — Full Analysis\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nknee_results = run_full_analysis(\n    knee_encoder, knee_train_clean_loader, knee_val_clean_loader,\n    knee_val_clean, knee_history, KNEE_SAVE, \"SimCLR-Knee\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"4c4f34a0","cell_type":"code","source":"del knee_encoder, knee_projector\ndel knee_train_loader, knee_val_loader\ndel knee_train_clean_loader, knee_val_clean_loader\nclear_gpu()","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"5658b72d","cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n# Part 2: Brain Only (IXI — Balanced T1 + T2)","metadata":{}},{"id":"48146e35","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PART 2: BRAIN — Data Loaders (balanced)\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nprint(\"Loading Brain datasets (balanced)...\")\naug = SimCLRAugmentMRI(IMG_SIZE)\n\nbrain_train_ds = MRISimCLRDataset(brain_train_paths, brain_train_labels, brain_label_map,\n                                   transform=aug, name=\"Brain-Train\")\nbrain_val_ds = MRISimCLRDataset(brain_val_paths, brain_val_labels, brain_label_map,\n                                 transform=aug, name=\"Brain-Val\")\n\nbrain_train_loader = DataLoader(brain_train_ds, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True,\n                                num_workers=NUM_WORKERS, pin_memory=True, drop_last=True)\nbrain_val_loader = DataLoader(brain_val_ds, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=False,\n                              num_workers=NUM_WORKERS, pin_memory=True)\n\nbrain_train_clean = MRICleanDataset(brain_train_paths, brain_train_labels, brain_label_map,\n                                     name=\"Brain-Train-Clean\")\nbrain_val_clean = MRICleanDataset(brain_val_paths, brain_val_labels, brain_label_map,\n                                   name=\"Brain-Val-Clean\")\n\nbrain_train_clean_loader = DataLoader(brain_train_clean, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE * 2, shuffle=False,\n                                      num_workers=NUM_WORKERS, pin_memory=True)\nbrain_val_clean_loader = DataLoader(brain_val_clean, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE * 2, shuffle=False,\n                                    num_workers=NUM_WORKERS, pin_memory=True)\n\nprint(f\"\\nTrain batches: {len(brain_train_loader)}\")\nprint(f\"Brain train: {len(brain_train_ds)} | Val: {len(brain_val_ds)}\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"e337b50a","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PART 2: BRAIN — Train SimCLR\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nBRAIN_SAVE = \"/kaggle/working/checkpoints/simclr_brain\"\nbrain_encoder, brain_projector, brain_history = train_simclr(\n    brain_train_loader, brain_val_loader, BRAIN_SAVE, model_name=\"SimCLR-Brain\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"5739344c","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PART 2: BRAIN — Full Analysis\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nbrain_results = run_full_analysis(\n    brain_encoder, brain_train_clean_loader, brain_val_clean_loader,\n    brain_val_clean, brain_history, BRAIN_SAVE, \"SimCLR-Brain\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"cdd85e4f","cell_type":"code","source":"del brain_encoder, brain_projector\ndel brain_train_loader, brain_val_loader\ndel brain_train_clean_loader, brain_val_clean_loader\nclear_gpu()","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"4cb267ab","cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n# Part 3: Combined (Knee + Balanced Brain)","metadata":{}},{"id":"7fc24a95","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PART 3: COMBINED — Data Loaders\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nprint(\"Loading Combined (Knee + balanced Brain) datasets...\")\naug = SimCLRAugmentMRI(IMG_SIZE)\n\ncomb_train_paths = knee_train_paths + brain_train_paths\ncomb_train_labels = knee_train_labels + brain_train_labels\ncomb_val_paths = knee_val_paths + brain_val_paths\ncomb_val_labels = knee_val_labels + brain_val_labels\n\ncomb_train_ds = MRISimCLRDataset(comb_train_paths, comb_train_labels, combined_label_map,\n                                  transform=aug, name=\"Combined-Train\")\ncomb_val_ds = MRISimCLRDataset(comb_val_paths, comb_val_labels, combined_label_map,\n                                transform=aug, name=\"Combined-Val\")\n\ncomb_train_loader = DataLoader(comb_train_ds, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True,\n                               num_workers=NUM_WORKERS, pin_memory=True, drop_last=True)\ncomb_val_loader = DataLoader(comb_val_ds, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=False,\n                             num_workers=NUM_WORKERS, pin_memory=True)\n\ncomb_train_clean = MRICleanDataset(comb_train_paths, comb_train_labels, combined_label_map,\n                                    name=\"Combined-Train-Clean\")\ncomb_val_clean = MRICleanDataset(comb_val_paths, comb_val_labels, combined_label_map,\n                                  name=\"Combined-Val-Clean\")\n\ncomb_train_clean_loader = DataLoader(comb_train_clean, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE * 2, shuffle=False,\n                                     num_workers=NUM_WORKERS, pin_memory=True)\ncomb_val_clean_loader = DataLoader(comb_val_clean, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE * 2, shuffle=False,\n                                   num_workers=NUM_WORKERS, pin_memory=True)\n\nprint(f\"\\nCombined train: {len(comb_train_ds)} slices, {len(comb_train_loader)} batches\")\nprint(f\"Combined val: {len(comb_val_ds)} slices\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"84dc6e0e","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PART 3: COMBINED — Train SimCLR\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nCOMBINED_SAVE = \"/kaggle/working/checkpoints/simclr_combined\"\ncomb_encoder, comb_projector, comb_history = train_simclr(\n    comb_train_loader, comb_val_loader, COMBINED_SAVE, model_name=\"SimCLR-Combined\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"e7eeb1ed","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PART 3: COMBINED — Full Analysis\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\ncomb_results = run_full_analysis(\n    comb_encoder, comb_train_clean_loader, comb_val_clean_loader,\n    comb_val_clean, comb_history, COMBINED_SAVE, \"SimCLR-Combined\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"b9139ce2","cell_type":"code","source":"del comb_encoder, comb_projector\ndel comb_train_loader, comb_val_loader\ndel comb_train_clean_loader, comb_val_clean_loader\nclear_gpu()","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"3eafcdfb","cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n# Summary & Comparison","metadata":{}},{"id":"11423592","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Cross-Model Comparison\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nprint(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 80)\nprint(\"  SIMCLR MODEL COMPARISON SUMMARY\")\nprint(\"=\" * 80)\n\nresults = {}\nfor name, save_dir in [(\"Knee\", KNEE_SAVE), (\"Brain\", BRAIN_SAVE), (\"Combined\", COMBINED_SAVE)]:\n    data = np.load(os.path.join(save_dir, \"scoring.npz\"), allow_pickle=True)\n    results[name] = {\n        \"train_knn\": data[\"train_knn\"],\n        \"val_knn\": data[\"val_knn\"],\n        \"val_feats\": data[\"val_feats\"],\n        \"thresh_knn\": float(data[\"threshold_knn_p95\"]),\n    }\n\nprint(f\"\\n{'Model':<12} {'Train μ':<10} {'Val μ':<10} {'Val σ':<10} {'p95 Thresh':<12} {'Val>p95':}\")\nprint(\"-\" * 70)\nfor name, r in results.items():\n    tr, vr = r[\"train_knn\"], r[\"val_knn\"]\n    flagged = (vr > r[\"thresh_knn\"]).sum()\n    print(f\"{name:<12} {tr.mean():<10.4f} {vr.mean():<10.4f} {vr.std():<10.4f} \"\n          f\"{r['thresh_knn']:<12.4f} {flagged}/{len(vr)} ({100*flagged/len(vr):.1f}%)\")\n\nprint(f\"\\n{'Model':<12} {'Feature STD':<14} {'Mean Cos Sim':<14} {'Status'}\")\nprint(\"-\" * 54)\nfor name, r in results.items():\n    feats = r[\"val_feats\"][:2000]\n    std = np.std(feats, axis=0).mean()\n    sim = np.dot(feats, feats.T)\n    off = sim[np.triu_indices_from(sim, k=1)].mean()\n    status = \"✅ Good\" if off < 0.9 else \"⚠️ High sim\"\n    print(f\"{name:<12} {std:<14.4f} {off:<14.4f} {status}\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"2788ff7e","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Comparative Plots\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(18, 5))\nfig.suptitle(\"SimCLR — Model Comparison\", fontsize=14, y=1.02)\n\ncolors = {\"Knee\": \"tab:blue\", \"Brain\": \"tab:orange\", \"Combined\": \"tab:green\"}\n\n# Load histories\nhistories = {}\nfor name, save_dir in [(\"Knee\", KNEE_SAVE), (\"Brain\", BRAIN_SAVE), (\"Combined\", COMBINED_SAVE)]:\n    ckpt = torch.load(os.path.join(save_dir, \"final.pt\"), map_location=\"cpu\", weights_only=False)\n    histories[name] = ckpt[\"history\"]\n\nfor name, h in histories.items():\n    axes[0].plot(h['train_loss'], label=f\"{name} train\", linewidth=2, color=colors[name])\n    axes[0].plot(h['val_loss'], label=f\"{name} val\", linewidth=2, color=colors[name], linestyle='--')\naxes[0].set_title('NT-Xent Loss'); axes[0].set_xlabel('Epoch')\naxes[0].legend(fontsize=7); axes[0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n\nfor name, r in results.items():\n    axes[1].hist(r['val_knn'], bins=50, alpha=0.5, label=name, color=colors[name])\naxes[1].set_title('Val kNN Scores'); axes[1].set_xlabel('Cosine Dist')\naxes[1].legend(); axes[1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n\nfor name, h in histories.items():\n    axes[2].bar(name, np.mean(h['epoch_time']), color=colors[name])\naxes[2].set_title('Avg Epoch Time (s)'); axes[2].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n\nfig.tight_layout()\nfig.savefig('simclr_comparison_plots.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\nplt.show()","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"06509531","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Zip & Download All Checkpoints\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nimport shutil\nfrom IPython.display import FileLink, display\n\nfor name, save_dir in [(\"knee\", KNEE_SAVE), (\"brain\", BRAIN_SAVE), (\"combined\", COMBINED_SAVE)]:\n    zip_path = shutil.make_archive(f\"simclr_{name}_checkpoints\", \"zip\",\n                                   root_dir=\".\", base_dir=save_dir)\n    size_mb = os.path.getsize(zip_path) / 1e6\n    print(f\"  {name}: {zip_path} ({size_mb:.1f} MB)\")\n    display(FileLink(zip_path))\n\nall_zip = shutil.make_archive(\"simclr_all_checkpoints\", \"zip\",\n                              root_dir=\".\", base_dir=\"/kaggle/working/checkpoints\")\nprint(f\"\\n  ALL: {all_zip} ({os.path.getsize(all_zip)/1e6:.1f} MB)\")\ndisplay(FileLink(all_zip))\n\nlog_time_budget(\"SESSION COMPLETE\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null}]}